    What are the types of images in digital image representation?
    The images types we will consider are: 1) binary, 2) gray-scale, 3) color, and 4) multispectral. Binary images are the simplest type of images and can take on two values, typically black and white, or 0 and 1. A binary image is referred to as a 1-bit image because it takes only 1 binary digit to represent each pixel.
